Only 18 municipalities received clean audits. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Auditors General's report on municipalities is out and it's not looking good. Only 18 municipalities received clean audits. Cooperative Governance Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma weighed in on this issue. READ: Municipalities are disregarding advice: Makwetu Dlamini-Zuma has stressed that the capacity and capability of people working in municipalities need to be improved. “It is not a good report, it shows that the state of municipalities is not healthy but as a new minister, I have to figure out what we have to do,” Dlamini-Zuma said. “One of the things that we may need to do is to build capacities and capabilities in the municipalities not only on financial management and supply chain management but generally on good governance.”